@startuml runtime-sequence-algedonic-escalation-fastpath-v1
title Algedonic Escalation Fast-Path (Application Runtime)

participant "Specialist Agent\nAPP-008" as APP_008
participant "LangGraph Orchestrator\nAPP-016" as APP_016
participant "PM Agent\nAPP-007" as APP_007
participant "CSCO Agent\nAPP-015" as APP_015
database "EventStore\nAPP-001" as APP_001

APP_008 -> APP_001: record_event(algedonic.raised, severity, context)
APP_016 -> APP_007: request emergency coordination context
APP_016 -> APP_015: invoke safety escalation review
APP_015 -> APP_001: record_event(decision.recorded, decision="contain|continue", correlation_id)

alt severity S1 / containment required
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(phase.suspended, correlation_id)
  APP_007 -> APP_001: record_event(review.pending)
else severity S2 / controlled continuation
  APP_016 -> APP_008: route containment or corrective handoff
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(decision.recorded, decision="continue-with-constraints", correlation_id)
else CSCO decision timeout/unavailable
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(phase.suspended, correlation_id)
  APP_016 -> APP_001: record_event(algedonic.escalated, reason="csco-decision-timeout", correlation_id)
end

APP_016 -> APP_001: create_snapshot("algedonic.raised")

note right of APP_015
Mapped to BPR-005 Algedonic Escalation and
BEV-005 Safety Signal Raised semantics.
Fail-safe control: on missing CSCO decision in time,
runtime defaults to containment/suspend path.
end note
@enduml
